<subSubSection pageId="69" pageNumber="70" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="69.[151,1437,473,966]" pageId="69" pageNumber="70">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,490,797,822]" pageId="69" pageNumber="70">Distribution and habitat</emphasis>
. 
<taxonomicName box="[506,800,797,822]" class="Gastropoda" family="Raphitomidae" genus="Pleurotomella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neogastropoda" pageId="69" pageNumber="70" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="eurybrocha">
<emphasis box="[506,800,797,822]" italics="true" pageId="69" pageNumber="70">Pleurotomella eurybrocha</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
ranges from the northeastern Atlantic to the 
<collectingRegion box="[1309,1388,798,822]" country="Portugal" name="Acores" pageId="69" pageNumber="70">Azores</collectingRegion>
and the Mediterranean, being a soft bottom dweller at bathyal depths, occasionally found at lower settings in the Mediterranean (
<bibRefCitation author="Panetta" box="[329,479,870,894]" pageId="69" pageNumber="70" refString="Panetta, P. (1971) Molluschi del Golfo di Taranto raccolti durante le crociere dell' &quot; Albatros &quot;. Annali del Museo Civico di Storia Naturale &quot; Giacomo Doria &quot;, 78, 149 - 180." type="journal article" year="1971">Panetta 1971</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Nordsieck" box="[491,673,869,894]" pageId="69" pageNumber="70" refString="Nordsieck, F. (1977) The Turridae of the European seas. La Piramide per La Conchiglia, Roma, 132 pp." type="book" year="1977">Nordsieck 1977</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Bouchet" box="[684,953,869,894]" pageId="69" pageNumber="70" refString="Bouchet, P. &amp; Waren, A. (1980) Revision of the Northeast Atlantic bathyal and abyssal Turridae (Mollusca, Gastropoda). The Journal of Molluscan Studies, supplement 8, 1 - 119. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.1093 / mollus / 46. supplement _ 8.1" type="journal article" year="1980">Bouchet &amp; Warén 1980</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Poppe" box="[964,1194,870,894]" pageId="69" pageNumber="70" refString="Poppe, G. T. &amp; Goto, Y. (1991) European Seashells. Volume I. (Polyplacophora, Caudofoveata, Solenogastra, Gastropoda). Verlag Christa Hemmen, Wiesbaden, 352 pp." type="book" year="1991">
Poppe &amp; 
<collectingRegion box="[1071,1127,870,894]" country="Malta" name="Zebbug" pageId="69" pageNumber="70">Goto</collectingRegion>
1991
</bibRefCitation>
). It was regarded as a characteristic element of the VP (bathyal mud) biocoenosis (
<bibRefCitation author="Di" box="[829,1109,905,930]" pageId="69" pageNumber="70" refString="Di Geronimo, I., Li Gioi, R. &amp; Sciacca, V. (1982) La fauna Pleistocenica dell'abbeveratoio Conzo (Grammichele, Catania). Geologica Romana, 21, 577 - 601." type="journal article" year="1982">
Di Geronimo 
<emphasis box="[986,1042,905,930]" italics="true" pageId="69" pageNumber="70">et al.</emphasis>
1982
</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
